Vice President Biden and Small Business Administration (SBA) Administrator Karen Mills will visit Wrap-Tite, Inc in Solon, Ohio to discuss the importance of the American Jobs Act for small businesses. They will also announce a new lending commitment. The Vice President will emphasize the need for Congress to pass the American Jobs Act in order to help small businesses grow and create more jobs. Wrap Tite, a manufacturer and distributor of packaging and shipping products, recently received an SBA loan to purchase a new facility. This has allowed them to continue growing, resulting in 5 new hires and $250,000 in equipment purchases over the last year.